From: jaewun <jaewun@users.noreply.github.com>
Subject: [PATCH] input: edt-ft5x06: allow retaining controller power in suspend

Thor's lower FT5452 touchscreen cannot safely take the driver's normal
reset/regulator poweroff path during deep suspend. Marking the node as
`wakeup-source` avoids that path because edt-ft5x06 returns early when
`device_may_wakeup()` is true, but it also causes I2C core to install and arm
the primary touch IRQ as a system wake IRQ.

That solves the poweroff/reset half of the problem while creating a second
failure mode: stray bottom-touch wake attribution during repeated deep short
probes. Add a small opt-in property that only retains the controller state
through suspend/resume. Boards can use it when the controller must remain
powered, but should not wake the SoC.
---
--- a/Documentation/devicetree/bindings/input/touchscreen/edt-ft5x06.yaml
+++ b/Documentation/devicetree/bindings/input/touchscreen/edt-ft5x06.yaml
@@ -60,6 +60,12 @@ properties:
 
   wakeup-source: true
 
+  edt,retain-power-in-suspend:
+    type: boolean
+    description:
+      Keep the controller powered and skip suspend/resume power sequencing,
+      without marking the interrupt as a system wake source.
+
   vcc-supply: true
   iovcc-supply: true
 
--- a/drivers/input/touchscreen/edt-ft5x06.c
+++ b/drivers/input/touchscreen/edt-ft5x06.c
@@ -142,6 +142,7 @@ struct edt_ft5x06_ts_data {
 	unsigned int crc_errors;
 	unsigned int header_errors;
 	bool no_regmap_bulk_read;
+	bool retain_power_in_suspend;
 };
 
 struct edt_i2c_chip_data {
@@ -1274,6 +1275,10 @@ static int edt_ft5x06_ts_probe(struct i2c_client *client)
 
 	tsdata->no_regmap_bulk_read =
 		device_property_read_bool(&client->dev, "no-regmap-bulk-read");
+	tsdata->retain_power_in_suspend =
+		device_property_read_bool(&client->dev,
+					  "edt,retain-power-in-suspend");
+
 	/*
 	 * Check which sleep modes we can support. Power-off requires the
 	 * reset-pin to ensure correct power-down/power-up behaviour. Start with
@@ -1416,7 +1424,7 @@ static int edt_ft5x06_ts_suspend(struct device *dev)
 	struct gpio_desc *reset_gpio = tsdata->reset_gpio;
 	int ret;
 
-	if (device_may_wakeup(dev))
+	if (device_may_wakeup(dev) || tsdata->retain_power_in_suspend)
 		return 0;
 
 	if (tsdata->suspend_mode == EDT_PMODE_NOT_SUPPORTED)
@@ -1458,7 +1466,7 @@ static int edt_ft5x06_ts_resume(struct device *dev)
 	struct edt_ft5x06_ts_data *tsdata = i2c_get_clientdata(client);
 	int ret = 0;
 
-	if (device_may_wakeup(dev))
+	if (device_may_wakeup(dev) || tsdata->retain_power_in_suspend)
 		return 0;
 
 	if (tsdata->suspend_mode == EDT_PMODE_NOT_SUPPORTED)
